    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Proposed School Budgets Would Raise Tax Rates</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Budgets proposed by Long Island school districts contain average increase of 4.7 percent in tax levy, down from 6.2 percent last year (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Budgets proposed by Long Island school districts for 2007-8 contain an average increase of 4.7 percent in the tax levy, down from 6.2 percent last year. Residents in the Island's 124 districts will vote on the proposed budgets on May 15. To look up the tax increase in a district, go to nytimes.com/intheregion.</p>
      </block>
